Courtesy #DStv403 KIMBERLY - The Department of Correctional Services is investigating the death of two inmates at Tswelopele Correctional centre in Kimberly. It's understood three inmates attacked a prison official with padlocks. When officials tried to intervene, a scuffle ensued and three inmates were injured. WATCH | SA prisons | Calls to rehabilitate inmates and facilities They were taken to an outside hospital, where two of them died. The other prisoner is receiving treatment.